CORTEZ OIL COMPANY v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 11, 1932. Wayne Johnson, of New York City, for petitioner. C. M. Charest, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and COTTERAL, Circuit Judges, and KENNAMER,- District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
